	<p>Last updated: July 15, 2026[cite: 38]</p>
	
	<p>At ErrorLedger, accessible from hakkoharvest.com, one of our main priorities is the privacy of our visitors[cite: 38]. This Privacy Policy document outlines the types of data that are processed, managed, or stored when you navigate our static post-mortem research platform[cite: 38].</p>

	<h3>Zero Personal Data Collection</h3>
	<p>Because ErrorLedger functions purely as a static, read-only educational reference library, we do not utilize account registrations, login portals, newsletter sign-ups, or custom user code collection forms[cite: 38]. We do not collect, process, or store personal identifiers, email addresses, database passwords, or private source code.</p>

	<h3>Log Files</h3>
	<p>ErrorLedger follows a standard procedure of using log files[cite: 38]. These files log visitors when they visit websites[cite: 38]. The information collected by log files includes internet protocol (IP) addresses, browser type, Internet Service Provider (ISP), date and time stamps, referring/exit pages, and possibly the number of clicks[cite: 38]. These are not linked to any personally identifiable information[cite: 39].</p>

	<h3>Cookies and Web Beacons</h3>
	<p>Like any other website, ErrorLedger uses "cookies"[cite: 38]. These cookies are used to store information including visitors' preferences, and the pages on the website that the visitor accessed or visited[cite: 38]. The information is used to optimize the users' experience by customizing our web page content based on visitors' browser type and/or other information[cite: 38].</p>

	<h3>Google DoubleClick DART Cookie</h3>
	<p>Google is one of the third-party vendors on our site[cite: 38]. It uses cookies, known as DART cookies, to serve ads to our site visitors based upon their visit to our domain and other sites on the internet[cite: 38]. Visitors can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting Google's Ads Settings[cite: 39].</p>

	<h3>Links to External Post-Mortems</h3>
	<p>Our incident records contain numerous hyperlinks leading directly to official vendor sites, security advisory boards, and public engineering blogs[cite: 39]. ErrorLedger does not control, administer, or assume liability for the data collection and privacy policies of these external platforms[cite: 39].</p>
